Quote: First came the Maori people sometime between the 8th and 14th centuries in  great seaward migrations across the Pacific Ocean... The Maori in effect became an under-class...  The final social transformation came in the 1940s and 50s with the import of American cultural and economic dominance - the automobile, urban migration, urban sprawl and a consumer culture.
